fix(mobile): hardening pass — gate Three.js *before* dynamic import

Follow-up audit caught that the previous emergency fix gated the
runtime init but Three.js still loaded on phones because Hero/Process/
Terms/InlineCTA statically imported the modules. The runtime gate
returned null without creating a renderer, but the phone had already
fetched + parsed the chunk. Same risk surface, just deferred.

Hardening:
  · New @lib/devicePolicy with isPhoneClassTouch() and
    shouldSkipHeavyVisuals() so the test lives in one place.
  · Hero.astro, InlineCTA.astro, process.astro, terms.astro now gate
    BEFORE dynamic import('@lib/prismGL' | '@lib/boxStar' | '@lib/
    founderCard' | '@lib/goldDust'). Phones never fetch Three.
  · Heavy modules (prismGL, katanaTrail, reelScene, goldDust, boxStar,
    founderCard) replaced their inline matchMedia checks with the
    shared shouldSkipHeavyVisuals() helper for consistency.
  · Services.astro + Reel.astro pin-skip now uses
    isPhoneClassTouch() ALONGSIDE the 720px media query — covers
    iPhone landscape (844px) and iPad portrait (820px) where
    coarse-pointer + touch makes the horizontal pin feel jerky.
  · responsive.css mobile InlineCTA: full-width row + center-aligned
    buttons + normal white-space — kills the last horizontal pixel
    overflow audit found at 390px.
  · CaseStudyLayout.astro now reads MDX frontmatter for title /
    description / canonical when props aren't passed directly. Fixes
    the empty-tag regression on /build-notes/. OG tags follow.

Verified:
  · npm run typecheck — 0 errors, 0 warnings, 3 known GA hints.
  · npm run build — clean.
  · dist/index.html: zero static refs to prismGL.*.js, three.module
    .*.js, or boxStar.*.js. Dynamic-only.
  · production: /build-notes/ now serves real <title>, <meta
    description>, <link canonical>, OG tags.

Phones get the cheap path. Desktop keeps the full Three.js prism.
iPad with magic keyboard keeps the full Three.js prism (fine pointer
breaks the gate). The whole point.
